Manage Your Stress! Tools to Stop Worrying & Start Living

The uncertainty of the implications of COVID-19 can take a toll on your mental health. The many challenges you are facing can easily elevate stress levels, so it‚Äôs important to learn how to cope effectively. People who can manage stress well are able to bring an optimistic outlook to their environments, have more positive mental well-being, and are able to help themselves and those around them.

What You‚Äôll Learn:

‚Ä¢ Basic Techniques in Analyzing Worry

What‚Äôs your favorite day of the week? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Tuesday is becoming a new favorite around here because we love sharing our team‚Äôs amazing stories with you for #TeamTuesday üòÄ

Today we invite you to learn more about Academic/Learning Coach Eva Ascencio‚Äôs love for science! ‚ù§Ô∏è

‚ÄúWhen my initial plan in college (medical school) did not work, I turned to ecological research. This experience was so fun because it tied in my love for the outdoors with biology and chemistry! It wasn‚Äôt until I went out and got my hands dirty that I realized the value of scientific research.‚Äù üåøüß™

üì∏‚ÄùResearch: We looked into the effects of increased salinity, due to sea level rise, in freshwater ecosystems. Specifically, we wanted to see how nitrogen, phosphorus, carbon and chlorophyll a (algae indicator) were affected by an increase of salt in the water.‚Äù -Eva Ascencio üíß üçè
